<subSubSection id="3294CD420759770A220656983C616884" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="D04B7015F1436034EC277AEBE011B553" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4B130DFF5D431986A21BCEAEE7DCDEE3" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
Differs from its closest Asian and North American relatives in the variously coloured but often bright lemon yellow pileus, similarly tinted stipe and smaller size, as well as in differences in sequence data produced for the transcription elongation factor (
<emphasis id="F73553CAA981AA5DEA43979A27776C9E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">tef</emphasis>
-1).
</paragraph>
